Hello all! This is it, the second greatest day of your life. Tickets for my latest tour, "Worst Daddy In The World," go on sale today. Like, right now. Right this very second.

David and I were both raised by moms who are educators helping to shape the minds of the next generation in vital ways. David’s mom was a teacher in the public school system for many years, and my mom has been a conflict resolution facilitator for both youth and adults through her decades-long work at the Topa Institute. David and I believe that the change and peace we all seek in the world starts with our kids valuing each other and the different cultures we all come from. To gather in a circle and hear each other’s histories and stories. If you’re looking for a way to support the efforts toward peace in this extremely painful and brutal time, please consider donating to Seeds of Peace, an organization that equips youth and educators from the Middle East to South Asia and beyond with the skills and relationships to work in solidarity across lines of difference to create more just and inclusive societies. Through their work, @SeedsOfPeace focuses on dialogue that shifts attitudes and perceptions in kids and builds respect and empathy for the next generation. 

When we talk about wanting peace for all people, here is a very real way to begin. 

www.SeedsOfPeace.Org
